<div class="container">
    <p class="about-me">I am a back-end web developer and software engineer. I live in the mountains of Colorado where I enjoy mountain biking and skiing, particularly xc skiing. I'm a former professional XC mountain biker and member of the U23 national mountain team. In 2016 I attended Turing School of Software and Design to pursue my passion for computer science and writing code. Later that same year I began work at Roaring Fork Internet Users Group(rof.net) working as the sole web developer and IT technician. There I supported and collaborated with clients in getting to the bottom of technical problems and issues and creating robust solutions.
I installed and set upwireless internet networks, offered multi-tiered technical support to our products, including web sites, wireless, basic OS issues and email and email server management. In the fall of 2017 I started work at Bluetent Marketing building and maintaining web sites as a backend web developer/support engineer. There I developed sites and features from proposal to polished end result. Performed root cause analysis and general to advanced troubleshooting on sites in development to production.</p> 
<br>
<p class="about-me">All throughout the time since Turing, I also have worked as a freelance web developer/software engineer, architecting applications throughout the entire app lifecycle, focussing on testing, coding, debugging and even hosting. When not working, I'm usually out riding my bike or skiing and playing in the mountains. 
    </p>
